display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>. For each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  E]]></fr:tex>, there is a radius <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r_{x}>0]]></fr:tex> such that the <fr:link
type="local"
href="ca-000L.xml"
addr="ca-000L"
title="Open Ball">Open Ball</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B_{r_{x}}(x)=\{y\in  Y\mid  d(x,y)<r_{x}\}\subseteq  E]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[V_{x}]]></fr:tex> be the set of all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  X]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y)<r_{x}]]></fr:tex> (i.e., <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[V_{x}]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r_{x}]]></fr:tex>-neighborhood of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>). Define
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[O=\bigcup _{x\in  E}V_{x}.]]></fr:tex>
Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[O]]></fr:tex> is an open subset of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> by the <fr:link
type="local"
href="ca-0015.xml"
addr="ca-0015"
title="Properties of open and closed subsets of metric spaces">Properties of open and closed subsets of metric spaces</fr:link>.</fr:p>
<fr:p>Since for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  E]]></fr:tex>, we see <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  V_{x}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E\subseteq  Y\cap  O]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p>By our choice of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[V_{x}]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[V_{x}\cap  Y=B_{x}\subseteq  E]]></fr:tex> for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex>. So <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[O\cap  Y\subseteq  E]]></fr:tex>. Thus <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E=Y\cap  O]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\Longleftarrow )]]></fr:tex> If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[O]]></fr:tex> is open in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E=Y\cap  O]]></fr:tex>, then every point <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  E\subseteq  O]]></fr:tex> has an open neighborhood <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[N_{x}\subseteq  O]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[N_{x}\cap  Y\subseteq  E]]></fr:tex>, so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is open relative to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><html:span
